{"lemma":"ظَهِيرَة","slug":"ظَهِيرَة","root":"ظ.ه.ر","root_slug":"ظ-ه-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ظ-ه-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ظَهِيرَة","root":"ظهر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27731"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B8%D9%8E%D9%87%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"noontime","examples":[{"text":"كان هناك الآلاف من البشر يتظاهرون تحت شمس الظهيرة اللاهبة.","english":"There were thousands of people demonstrating under the burning sun of noon."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ðˤa.hiː.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27731","headword_ar":"ظَهِيرَةٌ","root":"Zhr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"point of midday:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, K:) or only"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in summer:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haAjirapN","text_ar":"هَاجِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"midday in summer"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when the heat is vehement:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"period from a little before, to a little after, midday in summer:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"midday, when the sun declines from the meridian, at the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zuhor","text_ar":"ظُهْر"},{"kind":"text","text":": or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from its declining until the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSor","text_ar":"عَصْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, O, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haAjirap","text_ar":"هَاجِرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when the sun declines from the meridian:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehement heat of midday:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZuhorN","text_ar":"ظُهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (Az, TA:)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1930},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZahaAy^iru","text_ar":"ظَهَايِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atoyotuhu Had~a AlZ~ahiyrapi","text_ar":"اَتْيْتُهُ حَدَّ الظَّهِيرَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came to him at the point of midday in summer;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hiyna qaAma qaAy^imu AlZ~ahiyrapi","text_ar":"حِينَ قَامَ قَايِمُ الظَّهِيرَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when the sun had become high, and the shade had almost disappeared:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so expl. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qwm","text_ar":"قوم"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aborido Eanoka mina AlZ~ahiyrapi","text_ar":"اَبْرِدْ عَنْكَ مِنَ الظَّهِيرَةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Stay thou until the middayheat shall have become assuaged, and the air be cool."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fyH","text_ar":"فيح"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And hence, in a trad. of 'Omar, when a man came to him complaining of gout in the feet, he said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*abatoka AlZ~ahaAy^iru","text_ar":"كَذَبَتْكَ الظَّهَايِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Take thou to walking during the heat of the middays in summer."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","A","K","S","O","TA","Msb","IAth","Az"]}]}}